===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|buket}}, {{m|enm|boket}}, partly from {{der|en|ang|bucc}} {{gloss|"bucket, pitcher"; mod. dialectal {{m|en|buck}}}}, equivalent to {{suffix|bouk|et|lang=en}}; and partly from {{der|en|xno|buket}}, {{m|fro|buquet|t=tub; pail}} (compare {{cog|nrf|boutchet}}, {{cog|nrf|bouquet}}), diminutive of {{der|en|fro|buc|buc|abdomen; object with a cavity}}, from {{etyl|VL.|en}} {{m|la|*būcus}} (compare Occitan and {{m+|ca|buc}}, {{m+|it|buco}}, {{m|it|buca||hole, gap}}), from {{bor|en|frk|*buk|*būk|belly, stomach|notext=1}}. Both the Old English and Frankish terms derive from {{der|en|gem-pro|*būkaz||belly, stomach}}. More at {{l|en|bouk}}.

