===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[container]] made of [[rigid]] material, often with a [[handle]], used to [[carry]] liquids or small items.
#: ''I need a '''bucket''' to carry the water from the well.''
#* {{quote-text|year=1922|author={{w|Virginia Woolf}}|title={{w|Jacob's Room}}|chapter=1|passage=The crab was cool and very light. But the water was thick with sand, and so, scrambling down, Jacob was about to jump, holding his '''bucket''' in front of him, when he saw, stretched entirely rigid, side by side, their faces very red, an enormous man and woman.}}
# The [[amount]] held in this container.
#: ''The horse drank a whole '''bucket''' of water.''
# {{lb|en|UK|archaic}} A unit of measure equal to four [[gallon]]s.
# Part of a [[piece]] of [[machinery]] that [[resemble]]s a '''bucket'''.
# {{lb|en|slang}} An old [[car]] that is not in good working [[order]].
# {{lb|en|basketball|informal}} The [[basket]].
#: ''The forward drove to the '''bucket'''.''
# {{lb|en|basketball|informal}} A [[field]] [[goal]].
#: ''We can't keep giving up easy '''buckets'''.
# {{lb|en|variation management}} A mechanism for avoiding the [[allocation]] of targets in cases of [[mismanagement]].
# {{lb|en|computing}} A storage space in a [[hash table]] for every item sharing a particular [[key]].
# {{lb|en|informal|chiefly|plural}} A large amount of liquid.
#: ''It rained '''buckets''' yesterday.''
#: ''I was so nervous that I sweated '''buckets'''.''
# A [[bucket bag]].
#* '''1989''', Susan Ludwig, Janice Steinberg, ''Petite Style'' (page 46)
#*: Avoid bulky styles such as duffle sacks, '''buckets''', doctors' satchels, and hobos.

